**Local News Digest — Richmond, VA**

*Date: December 31, 2025*

1) **Richmond's RVA Illuminates Scaled Back Due to Weather** — The annual RVA Illuminates holiday lighting ceremony at Kanawha Plaza proceeded on December 5, 2025, despite adverse weather conditions. However, accompanying performances were canceled to ensure safety. ([rva.gov](https://www.rva.gov/parks-recreation-press-releases-and-announcements/news/city-richmond-announces-scale-back-rva?utm_source=openai))

2) **Dominion Energy Christmas Parade Returns with Extended Route** — On December 6, 2025, the Dominion Energy Christmas Parade featured an extended route starting at the Science Museum of Virginia, passing by the Children's Hospital of Richmond at VCU, and culminating at 10th Street. ([wtvr.com](https://www.wtvr.com/news/local-news/christmas-parade-preview-oct-31-2025?utm_source=openai))

3) **Richmond Reports $22 Million Budget Surplus** — The city announced a $22 million budget surplus for 2025, prompting discussions among city council members about potential tax rate adjustments. ([wtvr.com](https://www.wtvr.com/news/local-news/richmond-surplus-news-nov-18-2025?utm_source=openai))

4) **Mayor Avula Advances Transparency and Economic Growth** — On December 15, 2025, Mayor Danny Avula highlighted measures to enhance transparency, including the establishment of a Citywide Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) Library, and secured a $15 million investment from the Commonwealth of Virginia to support infrastructure improvements tied to CoStar Realty Information, Inc.'s facilities. ([rva.gov](https://www.rva.gov/press-releases-and-announcements/news/mayor-avula-advances-transparency-economic-growth-and-city?utm_source=openai))

5) **Local Organization Brings Holiday Support to Inmates** — Good News Global, a Richmond-based ministry, distributed thousands of Christmas Hope Packs to incarcerated individuals, correctional staff, and, where permitted, families of inmates across Virginia, including facilities in Fairfax County, Arlington County, Prince William-Manassas, Chesterfield County, and the Virginia Peninsula Regional Jail. ([m.richmondfreepress.com](https://m.richmondfreepress.com/news/2025/dec/24/local-organization-bringing-holiday-support-to-inmates/?utm_source=openai))

